<HEAD>Rebels Release Seven Captives In Philippines</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ZAMBOANGA, Philippines (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Moslem rebels Sunday released
seven civilians, including the wife and daughter of an American,
who were abducted a week ago in Basilan province near this southern
city, the military reported.
   The captives were freed at dawn in Sampinit village and brought
to the house of Basilan Gov. Gerry Salapuddin, who negotiated with
local Moslem rebel leader Rashid Kasim for their release, a
military report said.
