$50,000 ransom the kidnappers had demanded for each of them. Among
those released were Myrna Cawley, wife of American physician George
Cawley, and their daughter Catherine.
   The seven were among 11 civilians abducted by the rebels in an
ambush of three vehicles in Lamitan on Aug. 27.
   The rebels allowed 39 other people in the vehicles to go free.
Four of the kidnap victims were released Tuesday after their
relatives paid the rebels an undisclosed sum of money, the military
said.
