<2ND_LINE>AM-People,0681</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>People In The News</HEAD>
<HEAD>LaserPhoto NY44</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BANGKOK, Thailand (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Miss Universe 1988, Porntip
Nakhirunkanok of Thailand, said Sunday she is establishing a
foundation for needy children so they will know she won't desert
them when her reign is over.
   ``Children are just being turned away, (in) backyards, trash
cans and that's a nightmare, an absolute nightmare,'' said Porntip,
20.
   Porntip left Thailand at age 2 and grew up in southern
California, studying at Pasadena City College. She returned to
Bangkok Aug. 23 for a visit during which she has helped raise money
for orphans and other neglected children.
   ``Throughout my travels this year, I very much want to use my
personal celebrity to, in some small way, make a difference in the
lives of children of all nationalities,'' she said.
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>DALLAS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An engine on an airplane carrying musician Jerry
Jeff Walker and several band members caught fire while landing at
Dallas Love Field, but the fire was extinguished and no one was
hurt.
   ``As he was taxiing in, the right engine was on fire,'' said Len
Perryman, operations supervisor at the airport. He said didn't know
how the fire started.
   ``We're all right,'' Walker said of Saturday's mishap. ``We're
just worried about the plane, that's all. (The plane has) been
helping us all summer.''
   Walker, who has recorded on the MCA and Elektra labels and wrote
``Mr. Bojangles,'' said he was flying from Austin for a concert.
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>ATLANTIC CITY, N.J. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Albert A. Marks, Jr., the man
responsible for directing the course of the Miss America Pageant
over the past 35 years, is forcing himself to sit on the sidelines
this year now that he has retired.
   The former pageant director did not even come to the Convention
Center last week. Instead, he let the new executive director,
Leonard Horn, learn by trial and error.
   But Marks, 75, said he will attend the televised pageant
Saturday night in a box reserved for him, and he did allow himself
to attend a reception for the 51 contestants last week.
   Marks initially said he would stay on after his retirement to
assist Horn, but later decided ``I had to let go.''
   And besides, ``I'm still in the investment business, you know,''
he said.
