president the Rev. Carroll Luckenbaugh said Saturday.
   ``We're elated that he has been so impressed with the park when
he visited. We're really grateful,'' Luckenbaugh said.
   The funds are earmarked for a proposed $750,000 addition at the
park in this town situated between Harrisburg and Baltimore, he
said.
   Although it was Nixon's first visit to the park, it was not his
first contribution, officials said. Chief parks naturalist Kim
Young said ``he has supported us with donations throughout the
park's history.''
