   Republican nominee George Bush holds a
commanding lead over Democrat Michael Dukakis in the latest survey
of registered voters in Alabama, says a poll released Sunday.
   Bush is the favorite of slightly more than half of the 502
voters surveyed _ 50.7 percent _ while Dukakis is the choice of 34
