vice presidential nominee Lloyd Bentsen is qualified to be
president while 26.1 percent think Republican running mate Dan
Quayle has the skills and experience to run the country.
   Thirty percent, however, said they felt ``positive'' about
Quayle while 21.2 percent said they felt the same way about Bentsen.
