factories that pollute the environment, and they demand more
regional control over environmental and economic decisions.
   Bambitis did not say exactly where the protests took place in
Latvia.
   This summer, some of the Soviet Baltic coast's most popular
beaches, including Jurmala in Latvia, were closed to bathers
because of polluted water and refuse that washed up on shore.
